I stand before you today as the defendant, Lauren Dixon, pleading guilty to the charge of TV licence payment evasion. I would like to emphasize that this offense was not committed intentionally. I genuinely believed that the bill had been paid, only to discover later that I had 8 months of unlicensed use. Once I realized my mistake, I immediately rectified the situation by promptly purchasing a licence.

I want to bring to the court's attention that I have no previous criminal record. This is a testament to my upstanding character and commitment to abiding by the law. I have always strived to be a responsible and law-abiding citizen.

I want to assure the court that I am fully prepared to take all necessary measures to make amends for my actions. I understand the importance of fulfilling my obligations, and I am committed to rectifying the consequences of my mistake. I am willing to cooperate fully with any arrangements put forth by the court to ensure that I compensate for the harm caused.

In addition, I would like to express my deep regret for the inconvenience and any potential loss caused by my oversight. I understand the importance of the TV licence fee in supporting the broadcasting services, and I acknowledge that my failure to pay had a negative impact on this system.

Your Honor, I am pleading guilty today, and I believe that this in itself is a significant mitigating factor. I take full responsibility for my actions and understand the consequences that may follow. I stand here without excuses, ready to face the consequences of my mistake.

In conclusion, I respectfully request that the court consider the circumstances surrounding my offense, my lack of criminal history, and my immediate actions to rectify the situation. I assure the court of my commitment to fulfilling my responsibilities and making amends for any harm caused. I am hopeful that the court will take these factors into account when determining an appropriate sentence.

Thank you, Your Honor, for your time and consideration.

